Why don't you open it, Mert?
I always enjoy a good read after lunch.

716
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:20,113
JAN:
Sure, open it.

717
00:42:22,856 --> 00:42:23,845
All right.

718
00:42:24,024 --> 00:42:25,514
[CHUCKLES]

719
00:42:29,330 --> 00:42:30,763
JAN:
Oh.

720
00:42:30,998 --> 00:42:33,159
What is frontierism?

721
00:42:33,867 --> 00:42:36,665
Actually, I think
it's pronounced frotteurism.

722
00:42:36,837 --> 00:42:40,705
It's a deviant sexual behavior in which
the frotteur becomes sexually aroused...

723
00:42:40,874 --> 00:42:44,537
...by rubbing his genitals
against others in public places.

724
00:42:44,712 --> 00:42:47,579
-Oh.
-I read about it on the Internet.

725
00:42:47,748 --> 00:42:51,013
Do you subscribe to that magazine, Mert?

726
00:42:54,655 --> 00:42:56,885
Actually, I do.

727
00:42:57,091 --> 00:43:00,083
I have a client who is a frotteur.

728
00:43:00,261 --> 00:43:02,695
He's having a difficult time
overcoming his problem...

729
00:43:02,863 --> 00:43:06,959
...and I thought if I could understand
what it was like to be a frotteur...

730
00:43:07,134 --> 00:43:08,931
-...l'd be better prepared to help him.
-Oh.

731
00:43:10,304 --> 00:43:11,669
I mean, he is....

732
00:43:14,375 --> 00:43:16,969
He is such a good kid, darn it. Tsk.

733
00:43:17,144 --> 00:43:20,841
I just wanna help him get past this,
you know? Live up to his full potential.

734
00:43:21,015 --> 00:43:22,141
That's really cool.

735
00:43:22,316 --> 00:43:24,045
JAN: Thrilling is what it is.
MERT: Well....

736
00:43:24,518 --> 00:43:25,746
Moving.

737
00:43:26,987 --> 00:43:29,251
So, Nora.

738
00:43:29,890 --> 00:43:32,154
Did you study music in college?

739
00:43:32,326 --> 00:43:35,784
-I took a couple of guitar lessons.
-Mm!

740
00:43:35,963 --> 00:43:40,400
Jeffrey was accepted to
the Lunar Space Institute in Austin.

741
00:43:41,702 --> 00:43:43,465
Really?

742
00:43:43,637 --> 00:43:45,161
How was that?

743
00:43:45,339 --> 00:43:49,173
-Jeffrey didn't exactly finish.
-I cut my college experience short...

744
00:43:49,343 --> 00:43:52,710
...to save my mother the trauma
of empty nest syndrome, Mert.

745
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:54,040
JAN:
Cut it short, Jeffrey?

746
00:43:54,214 --> 00:43:56,876
No, no. Remember?
You showed me your dorm room...

747
00:43:57,051 --> 00:43:58,780
...and you made me take you home.

748
00:43:58,952 --> 00:44:02,353
It was like a prison cell. And did you see
who would've been my roommate?

749
00:44:02,523 --> 00:44:04,616
All covered in tattoos and piercings.

750
00:44:04,792 --> 00:44:08,626
I'm sure he and his friends would've gotten
intoxicated one night and sodomized me.

751
00:44:08,796 --> 00:44:09,956
Jeffrey.

752
00:44:10,130 --> 00:44:13,327
Sometimes we confuse our fears
with our fantasies, Jeffrey.

753
00:44:14,768 --> 00:44:16,998
I myself loved college.

754
00:44:17,171 --> 00:44:21,107
Getting away from my parents,
being on my own in Berkeley.

755
00:44:21,275 --> 00:44:23,334
I mean, it was a very exciting time.

756
00:44:23,510 --> 00:44:24,807
Mm. Heh.

757
00:44:24,978 --> 00:44:28,243
Berkeley in the '60s?
Must have been very exciting.

758
00:44:28,415 --> 00:44:31,612
All you hippies shooting up acid
and snorting LSD.

759
00:44:31,785 --> 00:44:36,722
I mean, I might have smoked a little pot,
but who hasn't, you know?

760
00:44:36,890 --> 00:44:39,154
I haven't.

761
00:44:39,326 --> 00:44:42,921
Neither have I. Because drugs are wrong.

762
00:44:43,097 --> 00:44:45,224
I tend to agree.

763
00:44:45,966 --> 00:44:48,560
Well, that was a long time ago.

764
00:44:50,337 --> 00:44:54,068
Nora? Do you make a living as a singer?

765
00:44:54,241 --> 00:44:56,209
Well, that's the dream.

766
00:44:56,377 --> 00:44:57,605
MERT:
What's holding you back?

767
00:44:57,778 --> 00:45:01,214
I'm just trying to save up enough money
so I can record a demo.

768
00:45:01,382 --> 00:45:03,373
But I can't afford it right now.

769
00:45:03,550 --> 00:45:06,485
I'm-- I'm sorry, what did--?
What did you say?

770
00:45:07,521 --> 00:45:09,011
I said I can't afford it.

771
00:45:09,189 --> 00:45:11,521
No, see, I still don't understand you...

772
00:45:11,692 --> 00:45:14,388
...because the word "can't"
isn't in my vocabulary.

773
00:45:15,062 --> 00:45:18,793
You see, Nora, I believe
that if you really want something in life...

774
00:45:18,966 --> 00:45:21,901
...you gotta go after it.
You can't let anything hold you back.

775
00:45:22,636 --> 00:45:24,763
-You just said "can't."
JAN: Uh-uh-- Mm.

776
00:45:24,938 --> 00:45:27,202
Jeffrey, please, just be quiet.

777
00:45:27,374 --> 00:45:30,434
I don't get it. I mean, how am I supposed
to record a demo...

778
00:45:30,611 --> 00:45:32,579
...if I don't have the money to pay for it?

779
00:45:32,746 --> 00:45:37,376
The future belongs to those who believe
in the beauty of their dreams.

780
00:45:39,787 --> 00:45:41,379
Lightning bolt. Lightning bolt.

781
00:45:41,555 --> 00:45:44,319
Lightning bolt. Lightning bolt.
Lightning bolt.

782
00:45:44,491 --> 00:45:46,925
Have pity, Gallantar,
I'm but a simple Mage.

783
00:45:47,094 --> 00:45:50,120
-Silver. Silver. Silver.
-Stop, I'm dead, Gallantar!

784
00:45:50,297 --> 00:45:54,165
-Enchanted. Enchanted.
-Stop, Gallantar! Time freeze! Ow!

785
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:55,631
Get off me. Get off.

786
00:45:55,803 --> 00:45:58,203
He called time freeze, Gallantar.
That means stop!

787
00:45:58,372 --> 00:46:02,206
I'm the game master, Rathkon.
I get to call the shots around here.

788
00:46:03,744 --> 00:46:05,109
You hit me in the forehead.

789
00:46:05,279 --> 00:46:08,715
I have a deposition tomorrow
and I'm gonna look ridiculous.

790
00:46:10,951 --> 00:46:12,646
What's wrong with you, Gallantar?

791
00:46:12,820 --> 00:46:15,311
Sorry, Alhorn, my old friend.

792
00:46:15,923 --> 00:46:18,391
I've brought my troubles
from home to the battlefield.

793
00:46:18,959 --> 00:46:20,119
The boyfriend?

794
00:46:23,130 --> 00:46:26,065
You must confront
this enemy head on, Gallantar.

795
00:46:27,034 --> 00:46:31,198
For your own sake,
and for the sake of the Land of Erdreja!

796
00:46:31,371 --> 00:46:33,362
[ALL CHEERING]

797
00:46:37,144 --> 00:46:38,668
Ahh.

798
00:46:39,346 --> 00:46:40,973
How do you like thine grog?

799
00:46:41,448 --> 00:46:44,042
It's not grog. This is apple juice.

800
00:46:44,218 --> 00:46:48,712
Well, yeah, I mean,
my parents locked the liquor cabinet, so I....

801
00:46:48,889 --> 00:46:50,686
It's got a lot of sugar in it, though, so....

802
00:46:50,858 --> 00:46:52,917
[ALL CHEER]

803
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:58,630
How may I help you elves?

804
00:46:58,799 --> 00:47:00,232
I'm looking for Mert Rosenbloom.

805
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:03,699
Why, are you trying to steal
the magic orbs?

806
00:47:10,277 --> 00:47:11,403
I'll call you back.

807
00:47:11,879 --> 00:47:12,868
[PHONE BEEPS]

808
00:47:13,046 --> 00:47:14,513
Wrong cord.

809
00:47:15,516 --> 00:47:17,984
-What's up, Lancelot?
-Your time in my life is up.

810
00:47:18,151 --> 00:47:20,642
My mother's not big enough
for the two of us.

811
00:47:20,821 --> 00:47:23,346
I'm sorry, Ace.
I love her, and I'm not leaving.

812
00:47:23,524 --> 00:47:25,719
Well, I'm not leaving either.

813
00:47:25,893 --> 00:47:29,294
You know, Jeffrey,
it doesn't have to be this way.

814
00:47:29,463 --> 00:47:31,226
I hereby throw down this gauntlet.

815
00:47:31,398 --> 00:47:33,491
[GLASS SHATTERING]

816
00:47:34,501 --> 00:47:36,025
MAN:
That sounds like glass.

817
00:47:36,203 --> 00:47:37,636
You're gonna pay for that.

818
00:47:39,172 --> 00:47:40,469
War is hell, old man.

819
00:47:40,641 --> 00:47:42,973
Yes, it is.

820
00:47:44,011 --> 00:47:45,945
And you're going down.

821
00:47:46,113 --> 00:47:47,603
That's a promise, son.

822
00:47:50,450 --> 00:47:52,281
See you on the battlefield.

823
00:48:02,529 --> 00:48:04,588
Don't call me son.

824
00:48:04,765 --> 00:48:07,131
So then I just went out
and got my tubes tied.

825
00:48:07,301 --> 00:48:10,031
Oh. You wanna go to Comic-Con?

826
00:48:10,203 --> 00:48:14,401
It's important to always create a kind
of positive atmosphere in the work home.

827
00:48:14,575 --> 00:48:16,509
And when I say "work home," I mean...

828
00:48:16,677 --> 00:48:19,612
...a place where you can have
a warm, kind of comfortable...

829
00:48:19,780 --> 00:48:21,771
...relaxing, kind of....

830
00:48:21,949 --> 00:48:23,814
You know,
an environment where people...

831
00:48:23,984 --> 00:48:26,953
...really enjoy what they're doing,
and it's--

832
00:48:28,555 --> 00:48:30,489
It's the kind of....

833
00:48:31,658 --> 00:48:34,855
It's the kind of thing that doesn't have--

834
00:48:35,028 --> 00:48:36,655
Goddamn it!

835
00:48:52,012 --> 00:48:53,445
Oh!

836
00:49:09,196 --> 00:49:10,561
[GRUNTS]

837
00:49:12,966 --> 00:49:14,797
[SCREAMING]

838
00:49:15,268 --> 00:49:16,599
Oh!

839
00:50:04,051 --> 00:50:05,313
[SIGHS]

840
00:50:05,485 --> 00:50:06,884
Oh.

841
00:50:15,562 --> 00:50:17,325
Mert?

842
00:50:17,731 --> 00:50:18,959
Uh-huh?

843
00:50:19,132 --> 00:50:21,066
What is this?

844
00:50:22,636 --> 00:50:25,002
It looks like a bong.

845
00:50:26,039 --> 00:50:28,064
Hmm. With some pot.

846
00:50:28,241 --> 00:50:32,109
That's what I thought,
but you said you don't do drugs anymore.

847
00:50:32,279 --> 00:50:35,646
-I don't.
-Well, then where'd this come from?

848
00:50:43,323 --> 00:50:47,987
Actually, the truth is...

849
00:50:49,129 --> 00:50:52,462
...I do smoke a little pot, once in a while.

850
00:50:52,666 --> 00:50:57,365
-Oh.
-Jan? It's not that, you know....

851
00:50:58,138 --> 00:51:00,504
Honesty is very important to me, Mert.

852
00:51:05,512 --> 00:51:07,377
[WHISPERS]
Mother fucking hell.

853
00:51:14,187 --> 00:51:16,280
Hello? Anyone home?

854
00:51:16,456 --> 00:51:18,447
[JAN SNIFFLING]

855
00:51:18,759 --> 00:51:20,192
Tsk. Oh....

856
00:51:21,728 --> 00:51:23,320
[CRYING]

857
00:51:23,497 --> 00:51:25,192
Hey, hey.

858
00:51:25,365 --> 00:51:27,230
Are you okay?

859
00:51:27,968 --> 00:51:29,959
What's the matter?

860
00:51:31,304 --> 00:51:34,034
Is it about Mert?

861
00:51:36,109 --> 00:51:41,513
Did you discover something
about him that you didn't know before?

862
00:51:41,681 --> 00:51:47,017
Well, I discovered that Mert smokes pot
because he has glaucoma...

863
00:51:47,187 --> 00:51:49,985
...but that's not actually it.

864
00:51:50,957 --> 00:51:54,051
Wait, then why are you crying?

865
00:51:55,662 --> 00:52:00,827
I'm crying because Mert and I
are gonna get married. Look. Ha-ha.

866
00:52:01,468 --> 00:52:02,662
[CORK POPS, JAN SQUEALS]

867
00:52:02,836 --> 00:52:05,498
Grab a glass. Let's celebrate, huh?

868
00:52:05,672 --> 00:52:08,402
You're gonna be a Rosenbloom.

869
00:52:08,575 --> 00:52:11,339
-Come on, baby, let's dance.
-Oh, Mert, no, I'm too embarrassed.

870
00:52:11,511 --> 00:52:12,569
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

871
00:52:12,746 --> 00:52:16,238
-Oh, no. Come on, come on, come on.
-Ah, sweetie, oh, please. Oh, Mert.

872
00:52:16,449 --> 00:52:18,474
JAN: Oh, ha-ha-ha.
MERT: Mm.

873
00:52:18,652 --> 00:52:20,882
Oh, you're so snappy, pappy.

874
00:52:21,922 --> 00:52:23,890
MERT: Ooh.
JAN: How's that?

875
00:52:24,057 --> 00:52:25,684
I feel like I'm on a subway.

876
00:52:25,859 --> 00:52:27,087
[BOTH LAUGH]

877
00:52:27,260 --> 00:52:29,194
Mert, what do you say?
Ha-ha-ha.

878
00:52:29,462 --> 00:52:31,453
[MERT GRUNTING]

879
00:52:32,165 --> 00:52:34,895
We got one other piece of good news.

880
00:52:35,936 --> 00:52:36,925
Jeffrey, dear?

881
00:52:37,103 --> 00:52:39,037
JEFFREY:
I can't believe you're selling the house.

882
00:52:39,206 --> 00:52:41,231
Look, we feel
it's in everyone's best interest.

883
00:52:41,408 --> 00:52:44,969
This is our home.
I spent my formative years here.

884
00:52:45,145 --> 00:52:47,670
No, of course it's your home, naturally...

885
00:52:47,848 --> 00:52:50,043
...but Mert and I are starting a new life...

886
00:52:50,217 --> 00:52:53,243
...and we want our own home
so that we can make new memories.

887
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:55,388
New memories.
Brand-new memories, Jeffrey.

888
00:52:55,555 --> 00:52:57,921
Well, I hate to rain on your parade...

889
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:01,288
...but I refuse to give my consent
on the sale of this house.

890
00:53:01,461 --> 00:53:04,862
Well, I don't need your consent
because the house is in my name.

891
00:53:05,031 --> 00:53:06,259
[SIGHS]

892
00:53:06,433 --> 00:53:11,268
Okay. Fine.
Let's assume for a moment that's true.

893
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:14,601
What about me?
Where do I fit into this new house equation?

894
00:53:14,774 --> 00:53:18,471
Well, we're looking at smaller places.

895
00:53:18,645 --> 00:53:21,136
Yeah, condos and whatnot. So....

896
00:53:21,314 --> 00:53:25,944
Yeah. No, but you can come and sleep in
the hideaway bed whenever you come for...

897
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:28,383
-...like, a little visit.
-Yeah, but, little.

898
00:53:28,555 --> 00:53:29,579
Visit?

899
00:53:29,756 --> 00:53:33,419
Don't worry, sweetie. I would be
so happy to subsidize you for a year...

900
00:53:33,593 --> 00:53:36,187
...two years, or three years,
or something like four--

901
00:53:36,363 --> 00:53:37,557
Or six months.

902
00:53:37,731 --> 00:53:42,134
Six months. As long as it takes
for you to learn how to pay for things.

903
00:53:42,302 --> 00:53:45,499
Fine. You two obviously
don't want me here anymore...

904
00:53:45,672 --> 00:53:47,970
...so maybe I'll just
get out of your hair tonight.

905
00:53:48,141 --> 00:53:50,234
Jeffrey, no.

906
00:53:50,410 --> 00:53:51,843
Yeah.

907
00:53:52,012 --> 00:53:53,775
Mert.

908
00:53:54,281 --> 00:53:56,272
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER STEREO]

909
00:53:57,284 --> 00:53:59,309
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

910
00:54:04,791 --> 00:54:05,815
NORA:
Hey.

911
00:54:05,992 --> 00:54:09,428
Thank goodness you're home.
I'm in desperate need of a Yoo-hoo.

912
00:54:09,596 --> 00:54:13,828
I have this nasty infestation of vermin at my
house which I can't seem to exterminate...

913
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:16,161
...and it's causing my gastritis to flare up.

914
00:54:16,336 --> 00:54:18,702
Yoo-hoo's the only beverage
that seems to soothe it.

915
00:54:18,872 --> 00:54:20,464
How do you know where I live?

916
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:24,201
I bribed one of your associates
with a discount card.

917
00:54:25,011 --> 00:54:28,071
Well, unfortunately,
I'm fresh out of Yoo-hoo.

918
00:54:28,248 --> 00:54:29,647
[EXHALES]

919
00:54:30,750 --> 00:54:32,217
[SIGHS]

920
00:54:36,289 --> 00:54:37,415
[SIGHS]

921
00:54:37,590 --> 00:54:40,150
I see you still listen to Morrissey.

922
00:54:40,327 --> 00:54:43,160
Yeah, well,
a lot of his new stuff's really good.

923
00:54:43,330 --> 00:54:45,457
Really? I wouldn't know.

924
00:54:45,632 --> 00:54:49,227
He's been dead to me since 1987
when The Smiths broke up.

925
00:54:49,402 --> 00:54:54,931
How old were you? Like, 10?
You should really give him another shot.

926
00:54:55,976 --> 00:54:57,375
[MUSIC STOPS]

927
00:54:57,777 --> 00:55:01,770
[MORRISSEY'S "AMERICA IS NOT
THE WORLD" PLAYING OVER STEREO]

928
00:55:21,901 --> 00:55:24,699
So, what do you think?

929
00:55:24,871 --> 00:55:27,772
It's not atrocious.

930
00:55:28,908 --> 00:55:31,376
I think you're better.

931
00:55:34,247 --> 00:55:36,238
[CHUCKLES]
Thanks.

932
00:55:47,627 --> 00:55:49,458
Do you want some?

933
00:55:50,463 --> 00:55:52,363
Marijuana?!

934
00:55:52,532 --> 00:55:55,933
I'm sorry, I say no to drugs
and so should you.

935
00:55:57,537 --> 00:55:59,437
-Are you joking?
-No.

936
00:55:59,606 --> 00:56:05,203
Not only is it illegal, I'm sure it contains
any number of unknown toxic substances.

937
00:56:06,012 --> 00:56:10,813
But go ahead and "trip out"
or whatever it is you hippies do.

938
00:56:10,984 --> 00:56:15,546
I'll just sit here and monitor you
for safety purposes.

939
00:56:16,389 --> 00:56:19,187
Well, it's a good thing you're here.

940
00:56:26,733 --> 00:56:29,201
You're kind of a freak.

941
00:56:30,103 --> 00:56:32,128
Thank you.

942
00:56:32,806 --> 00:56:34,865
[HISSING THROUGH TEETH]

943
00:56:35,842 --> 00:56:37,707
Mooo.

944
00:56:39,712 --> 00:56:41,111
[CHUCKLES]

945
00:56:46,286 --> 00:56:51,417
Maya, it's Mert again.
I was really hoping that we could talk.

946
00:56:51,591 --> 00:56:55,721
Listen, I'm not sure
why you sent my letter back, but....

947
00:56:58,465 --> 00:57:01,923
I wanna see you, that's all.
All right, I just-- I wanna see you.

948
00:57:02,102 --> 00:57:05,765
So, call me, please. I love you.

949
00:57:10,243 --> 00:57:11,505
[PHONE BEEPS]

950
00:57:44,878 --> 00:57:49,338
Seymour, I need a six-week advance on
my salary so I can purchase a plane ticket.

951
00:57:49,516 --> 00:57:51,347
I'm letting you go, Jeffrey.

952
00:57:51,518 --> 00:57:53,713
-What?
-I'm sorry.

953
00:57:53,887 --> 00:57:56,378
You can't fire me. I'm irreplaceable.

954
00:57:56,556 --> 00:57:58,786
I'm replacing you with Keith.

955
00:57:58,958 --> 00:58:01,791
Don't do this to me, all right?
I love this old bookstore.

956
00:58:01,961 --> 00:58:04,054
Here's your severance check.

957
00:58:05,198 --> 00:58:06,825
I gave you my youth, Seymour.

958
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:11,528
-If you need a reference, I'd be happy to--
-Burn in hell, old man!

959
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:19,341
NORA [SINGING] :
<i>'Cause I believe that freedom's</i>

960
00:58:19,512 --> 00:58:22,845
<i>A right that we all share</i>

961
00:58:23,016 --> 00:58:26,508
<i>But I believe that advertising's</i>

962
00:58:26,686 --> 00:58:29,814
<i>Messing up our air</i>

963
00:58:30,557 --> 00:58:36,985
<i>And when I see a Nike swoosh</i>
<i>On a baseball player's mitt</i>

964
00:58:37,163 --> 00:58:39,597
<i>Hah</i>
<i>It makes me bawl</i>

965
00:58:39,766 --> 00:58:42,166
<i>'Cause the world is all</i>

966
00:58:42,335 --> 00:58:44,360
<i>Bed, Bath and Bullshit</i>

967
00:58:44,537 --> 00:58:46,971
Nora? Nora?

968
00:58:47,140 --> 00:58:49,040
I need you to drive me to Arizona.

969
00:58:49,209 --> 00:58:52,269
What are you doing here?
You just ruined a great take.

970
00:58:52,445 --> 00:58:55,278
Do you have any idea
how hard it is to record a good demo?

971
00:58:57,650 --> 00:58:58,810
What is this?

972
00:58:58,985 --> 00:59:01,510
