973
00:59:02,555 --> 00:59:04,819
Go ahead, take a gander.

974
00:59:05,925 --> 00:59:08,792
I don't know. I just....

975
00:59:08,962 --> 00:59:10,827
Mert doesn't really seem
like the cheating type.

976
00:59:10,997 --> 00:59:12,225
[CHUCKLES]

977
00:59:12,398 --> 00:59:14,832
-They never do.
-So, what do you need me for, anyway?

978
00:59:15,001 --> 00:59:16,901
Why don't you just
show those emails to your mom?

979
00:59:17,070 --> 00:59:20,164
Uh-uh. Too circumstantial.
We need definitive evidence.

980
00:59:20,340 --> 00:59:22,831
Nothing must be left to chance.
Now, come on, let's go.

981
00:59:23,009 --> 00:59:25,705
Jeffrey! I'm in the middle
of recording my demo.

982
00:59:25,878 --> 00:59:28,540
Nora, time is not our friend at the moment.

983
00:59:28,715 --> 00:59:32,481
My mother's gonna marry that philanderer
if we don't do something right now.

984
00:59:35,955 --> 00:59:37,445
Please.

985
00:59:37,624 --> 00:59:40,559
I'm just trying to do
what's best for my mother.

986
00:59:40,727 --> 00:59:43,423
I could really use your help.

987
00:59:44,430 --> 00:59:46,762
Arizona?

988
01:00:01,781 --> 01:00:03,180
[SIGHS]

989
01:00:03,349 --> 01:00:05,340
[BREATHING LOUDLY]

990
01:00:06,953 --> 01:00:09,751
Hey. Hey.

991
01:00:10,023 --> 01:00:11,547
[GASPS]

992
01:00:11,724 --> 01:00:13,157
I'm gonna stop, okay?

993
01:00:13,326 --> 01:00:15,692
Stop where?

994
01:00:15,862 --> 01:00:18,524
I don't know. I was thinking
we could camp out tonight.

995
01:00:18,698 --> 01:00:20,165
You know, under the stars.

996
01:00:20,333 --> 01:00:22,358
I've got a couple sleeping bags
in the back.

997
01:00:22,535 --> 01:00:23,661
Camp out?

998
01:00:23,836 --> 01:00:26,964
I don't wanna be raped
by some sex-crazed trucker.

999
01:00:30,810 --> 01:00:35,304
Come on. Why don't you drive? For real.

1000
01:00:46,626 --> 01:00:48,116
I know about fat camp.

1001
01:00:49,762 --> 01:00:51,286
It's okay.

1002
01:00:51,464 --> 01:00:55,457
I was a chunky kid too. Believe me,
I know exactly what you went through.

1003
01:00:55,635 --> 01:00:57,626
It's awful.

1004
01:01:00,907 --> 01:01:02,807
Just be honest with me.

1005
01:01:10,116 --> 01:01:16,214
I'm afraid to drive because
my father was killed in a car accident.

1006
01:01:16,389 --> 01:01:18,050
Okay?

1007
01:01:20,993 --> 01:01:22,927
I'm sorry.

1008
01:01:40,446 --> 01:01:42,641
-This is pretty great, huh?
-Oh, yeah.

1009
01:01:42,815 --> 01:01:45,181
If you consider great
having a sciatica flare-up...

1010
01:01:45,351 --> 01:01:47,512
...while being eaten alive by mosquitoes.

1011
01:01:47,687 --> 01:01:50,019
Don't be such a baby.

1012
01:01:51,290 --> 01:01:54,691
I can't believe
you've never been camping before.

1013
01:01:54,861 --> 01:01:59,127
I've been camping.
Just never without adult supervision.

1014
01:01:59,298 --> 01:02:00,595
[CHUCKLES]

1015
01:02:01,901 --> 01:02:04,802
My father took me once when I was 10.

1016
01:02:05,838 --> 01:02:12,141
Actually, that's the first time I heard
the seductive song of the astronomy siren.

1017
01:02:13,045 --> 01:02:14,876
NORA:
That's cool.

1018
01:02:15,047 --> 01:02:20,314
My dad was too busy getting hammered and
puking on his shoes to take me anywhere.

1019
01:02:22,221 --> 01:02:24,485
His loss.

1020
01:02:38,671 --> 01:02:42,232
I just feel so insignificant out here.

1021
01:02:43,376 --> 01:02:45,310
Don't you?

1022
01:02:46,245 --> 01:02:49,112
Sometimes.

1023
01:02:49,282 --> 01:02:54,413
But then other times
I feel totally connected to the universe...

1024
01:02:54,587 --> 01:02:59,547
...like a part of something
greater than myself, or even this planet.

1025
01:02:59,725 --> 01:03:04,355
That despite what happens to all of us
when we shuffle off this mortal coil...

1026
01:03:04,530 --> 01:03:06,555
...the universe will still be here.

1027
01:03:11,771 --> 01:03:13,602
That was beautiful.

1028
01:03:13,773 --> 01:03:17,675
Yes, well, I'm paraphrasing
Leonard Nimoy, of course.

1029
01:03:17,844 --> 01:03:19,436
[GULPS]

1030
01:03:22,215 --> 01:03:24,206
[TEETH CHATTERING]

1031
01:03:27,453 --> 01:03:29,182
Are you okay?

1032
01:03:29,355 --> 01:03:31,346
What do you mean?

1033
01:03:32,425 --> 01:03:34,791
Your teeth are chattering.

1034
01:03:34,961 --> 01:03:36,155
They are?

1035
01:03:36,329 --> 01:03:38,422
Are you cold?

1036
01:03:38,598 --> 01:03:41,123
Not particularly.

1037
01:03:44,837 --> 01:03:46,600
Is that a permanent retainer?

1038
01:03:47,907 --> 01:03:50,569
-Yeah.
-I have one too.

1039
01:03:50,743 --> 01:03:52,608
See?

1040
01:03:54,380 --> 01:03:57,838
They say you're supposed to
keep it in for life, you know?

1041
01:03:58,017 --> 01:04:01,475
Well, that's what my orthodontist said.

1042
01:04:21,107 --> 01:04:23,098
[BIRDS TWEETING]

1043
01:04:28,881 --> 01:04:30,508
Hey.

1044
01:04:33,185 --> 01:04:36,086
So ready to go?

1045
01:04:47,466 --> 01:04:49,229
-Hold on!
-Come on.

1046
01:04:50,770 --> 01:04:52,328
[WHISPERS]
Jeffrey?

1047
01:04:52,505 --> 01:04:55,269
Jeffrey, what are we doing?
She's in a meeting.

1048
01:04:55,441 --> 01:04:57,409
Not for long.

1049
01:04:57,810 --> 01:05:00,040
[WOMAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

1050
01:05:00,212 --> 01:05:04,148
Sorry to interrupt.
I have an urgent message for Maya Sinclair.

1051
01:05:04,317 --> 01:05:06,308
I'm Maya Sinclair. What is it?

1052
01:05:06,485 --> 01:05:09,386
Does the name Mert Rosenbloom
mean anything to you?

1053
01:05:09,555 --> 01:05:11,955
What happened? Is he all right?

1054
01:05:12,124 --> 01:05:16,720
I don't know, you tell me. You're the one
who's been sleeping with him.

1055
01:05:16,896 --> 01:05:17,885
[WOMAN CLEARS THROAT]

1056
01:05:18,064 --> 01:05:21,625
You sick bastard. Bob, call Security.

1057
01:05:21,801 --> 01:05:22,825
Me, sick?

1058
01:05:23,002 --> 01:05:26,267
You're the one having an affair with
a man who's engaged to another woman.

1059
01:05:26,439 --> 01:05:29,272
Mert Rosenbloom is not my lover,
you psycho. He's my father.

1060
01:05:29,442 --> 01:05:31,433
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

1061
01:05:35,581 --> 01:05:37,811
The last time I saw Mert,
I was 12 years old.

1062
01:05:37,984 --> 01:05:42,318
He dropped me off for soccer practice
one day and never came back.

1063
01:05:42,488 --> 01:05:46,185
At the time, my mom told me
that he just wasn't ready to be a father.

1064
01:05:46,359 --> 01:05:50,955
And when I was older, she told me
that he suffered from depression.

1065
01:05:51,130 --> 01:05:53,121
He started emailing me
a couple years ago...

1066
01:05:53,299 --> 01:05:55,563
...telling me that
he'd turned his life around...

1067
01:05:55,735 --> 01:05:58,499
...and that he'd become
some sort of motivational speaker.

1068
01:05:58,671 --> 01:06:02,368
Actually, I think
he prefers the term "success coach."

1069
01:06:04,010 --> 01:06:08,538
He said that he met this really great woman
and he wanted me to meet her.

1070
01:06:08,714 --> 01:06:10,875
So when I didn't respond, I guess...

1071
01:06:11,050 --> 01:06:14,076
...he just figured
he'd rather say he didn't have any kids...

1072
01:06:14,253 --> 01:06:16,585
...than admit that he'd messed up so bad.

1073
01:06:16,756 --> 01:06:18,485
Maybe I should have responded.

1074
01:06:18,658 --> 01:06:20,182
I don't know.

1075
01:06:20,359 --> 01:06:24,159
I guess I just never figured out
a way to forgive him.

1076
01:06:35,608 --> 01:06:37,269
NORA:
We're here.

1077
01:06:38,744 --> 01:06:39,938
[SIGHS]

1078
01:06:40,112 --> 01:06:45,243
Well, I feel sorry for the poor guy.

1079
01:06:45,418 --> 01:06:48,319
But the truth must be revealed.

1080
01:06:48,487 --> 01:06:52,480
Wait a minute. You still want your mom
to break up with him?

1081
01:06:52,658 --> 01:06:54,250
The man lied to her, Nora.

1082
01:06:54,427 --> 01:06:57,396
-He was ashamed.
-A lie is a lie.

1083
01:06:57,563 --> 01:07:00,760
Ugh. Wait a minute.
So you've never told a lied before?

1084
01:07:00,933 --> 01:07:01,957
Absolutely not.

1085
01:07:02,134 --> 01:07:05,695
That's a lie right there.
Remember fat camp?

1086
01:07:05,871 --> 01:07:08,169
That's different.

1087
01:07:11,811 --> 01:07:14,279
What about Allison?

1088
01:07:14,447 --> 01:07:15,880
What about her?

1089
01:07:16,048 --> 01:07:20,382
I know there is no Allison.
Mert told me all about it.

1090
01:07:20,553 --> 01:07:22,487
And you believed him?

1091
01:07:22,655 --> 01:07:25,522
The man will stop at nothing
to bring me down. Don't you see?

1092
01:07:25,691 --> 01:07:29,525
That's what this whole crusade is all about,
saving my mother from that monster.

1093
01:07:29,695 --> 01:07:32,789
You're not trying to save your mom,
you're trying to sabotage her...

1094
01:07:32,965 --> 01:07:34,899
...because you're too afraid to grow up.

1095
01:07:35,067 --> 01:07:37,467
And I was just a pawn
in your sick little plan.

1096
01:07:37,636 --> 01:07:41,163
You were not a pawn.
You were an essential component.

1097
01:07:41,340 --> 01:07:44,366
An essential component?

1098
01:07:45,244 --> 01:07:47,235
Is that what you think of me?

1099
01:07:47,413 --> 01:07:49,347
Yeah. What's wrong with that?

1100
01:07:50,816 --> 01:07:52,943
You're such an asshole.

1101
01:07:53,119 --> 01:07:54,347
Get out.

1102
01:07:55,955 --> 01:07:59,015
-Okay, Nora, I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.
-Get out!

1103
01:08:05,097 --> 01:08:06,086
[KEYS JINGLE]

1104
01:08:06,265 --> 01:08:08,028
[ENGINE STARTS]

1105
01:08:26,118 --> 01:08:27,449
[DOOR CLOSES]

1106
01:08:33,292 --> 01:08:35,021
Morning, Jeffrey.

1107
01:08:35,194 --> 01:08:36,752
Oh, Mert.

1108
01:08:36,929 --> 01:08:39,523
That's my name, don't wear it out.

1109
01:08:39,698 --> 01:08:41,723
What are you doing up?

1110
01:08:42,668 --> 01:08:44,135
Cut the bullshit.

1111
01:08:45,805 --> 01:08:49,036
I know where you've been,
and you shouldn't have gone there.

1112
01:08:49,208 --> 01:08:53,110
Well, you shouldn't have
told Nora about Allison.

1113
01:08:53,279 --> 01:08:55,873
Stay away from me, you maniac.

1114
01:08:56,048 --> 01:08:57,276
I'll call the police.

1115
01:08:57,449 --> 01:08:59,679
Go ahead. It'll be over
by the time they get here.

1116
01:08:59,852 --> 01:09:02,650
I'll scream. My mother's not gonna
stand idly by while you murder me.

1117
01:09:02,822 --> 01:09:04,289
[GRUNTS]

1118
01:09:05,124 --> 01:09:07,058
Scared you.

1119
01:09:07,860 --> 01:09:09,555
[LAUGHS]

1120
01:09:14,700 --> 01:09:16,497
Come on. Ha-ha-ha-ha.

1121
01:09:17,503 --> 01:09:19,266
Don't make me hurt you, mama's boy.

1122
01:09:19,438 --> 01:09:23,238
Bring it on, old man, if you can
even see me with your glaucoma.

1123
01:09:23,409 --> 01:09:24,774
Whoa, whoa! Woop!

1124
01:09:24,944 --> 01:09:26,935
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1125
01:09:32,017 --> 01:09:34,178
You ever been in a fight before, crybaby?

1126
01:09:34,353 --> 01:09:36,014
As a matter of fact, I have. Huh? Huh?

1127
01:09:36,188 --> 01:09:39,954
[SCREAMS]

1128
01:09:40,125 --> 01:09:42,457
[BOTH SCREAMING]

1129
01:09:46,799 --> 01:09:49,461
What the hell is going on here?
What's going on?

1130
01:09:49,635 --> 01:09:51,603
What? Huh?

1131
01:09:51,770 --> 01:09:53,169
-He started it.
-I did not.

1132
01:09:53,339 --> 01:09:54,431
-Did too.
-I did not!

1133
01:09:54,607 --> 01:09:55,869
-Did too.
-I did not!

1134
01:09:56,041 --> 01:09:58,601
Stop! Will somebody please...

1135
01:09:58,777 --> 01:10:00,540
[MERT AND JEFFREY PANTING]

1136
01:10:00,713 --> 01:10:03,648
...in God's name,
tell me what is going on here?

1137
01:10:04,316 --> 01:10:08,446
Mert lied to you, Mother.
He has a daughter, and I have proof.

1138
01:10:09,788 --> 01:10:11,653
Mert, what is he talking about?

1139
01:10:11,824 --> 01:10:13,621
[STAMMERING]
Well, I mean-- I was--

1140
01:10:13,792 --> 01:10:17,193
I was going to-- I was going to tell you.

1141
01:10:17,363 --> 01:10:20,457
Okay, forget it. Forget it. Here.
You can take your ring back, Mert.

1142
01:10:20,633 --> 01:10:22,601
-Yes.
-I'm not gonna take it. I am not--

1143
01:10:22,768 --> 01:10:25,737
-Jan, I am not-- I am not taking the ring.
-And good luck.

1144
01:10:25,905 --> 01:10:29,363
-Jan, your son--
-Don't talk to me like that.

1145
01:10:29,541 --> 01:10:34,877
Don't you dare say that about my son!
Okay, that's it, Mert. I've had it!

1146
01:10:35,047 --> 01:10:36,878
Put him on a leash!

1147
01:10:39,051 --> 01:10:41,042
[CRYING]

1148
01:10:45,991 --> 01:10:49,222
I know it wasn't easy for you
to break it off with him, Mother...

1149
01:10:49,395 --> 01:10:52,694
...but take comfort in the fact
that you did the right thing.

1150
01:10:52,865 --> 01:10:55,959
No one should have
to cohabitate with a liar.

1151
01:10:58,537 --> 01:10:59,697
Oh, and...

1152
01:10:59,872 --> 01:11:03,740
...I was thinking that maybe for dinner
tonight we could do something special.

1153
01:11:03,909 --> 01:11:05,376
Jeffrey?

1154
01:11:09,782 --> 01:11:11,875
I want you to move out.

1155
01:11:13,519 --> 01:11:14,713
What?

1156
01:11:14,887 --> 01:11:18,914
You have two weeks, Jeffrey,
to find your own place. I'm sorry.

1157
01:11:19,758 --> 01:11:22,226
No, I'm not leaving. You can't make me.

1158
01:11:22,394 --> 01:11:23,725
Yes, I can, Jeffrey.

1159
01:11:25,030 --> 01:11:28,022
All right, fine, I'm sorry.
I'll be better. I promise.

1160
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:29,633
It's too late for that, Jeffrey.

1161
01:11:29,802 --> 01:11:33,533
No, look, you're in a state of shock,
you don't know what you're saying.

1162
01:11:33,706 --> 01:11:38,166
I know exactly what I'm saying.
Now, please let go of me. Let go of me.

1163
01:11:40,546 --> 01:11:42,878
Fine. You want me to leave?

1164
01:11:43,048 --> 01:11:46,108
I don't need your pity fortnight.
I'll leave right now.

1165
01:11:46,285 --> 01:11:50,551
But I want you to know you're right.
This is all your fault.

1166
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:55,820
That I turned out this way,
that you used me to replace Dad.

1167
01:12:00,032 --> 01:12:01,465
Oh.

1168
01:12:03,068 --> 01:12:04,433
[SIGHS]

1169
01:12:04,603 --> 01:12:07,037
Oh. Oh, dear.

1170
01:12:09,241 --> 01:12:11,106
Here.

1171
01:12:37,102 --> 01:12:38,569
[DOOR CLOSES]

1172
01:12:42,541 --> 01:12:44,338
[SIGHS]

1173
01:12:47,413 --> 01:12:48,812
What do you want?

1174
01:12:50,282 --> 01:12:54,116
Actually, I'd like an application
for employment.

1175
01:12:54,286 --> 01:12:57,153
I'm looking for work,
and I recalled you mentioning...

1176
01:12:57,322 --> 01:13:00,416
...that the benefits package
here was respectable.

1177
01:13:00,592 --> 01:13:03,720
Hey, Richard, can you
bring this guy out an application?

1178
01:13:03,896 --> 01:13:05,693
The manager will be right with you.

1179
01:13:07,399 --> 01:13:10,835
Hey, if you wanna just fill this out
for me right there--

1180
01:13:12,304 --> 01:13:14,704
So how are things?

1181
01:13:14,873 --> 01:13:17,865
Can you cover for me?
I'm gonna take off early.

1182
01:13:18,043 --> 01:13:21,706
Nora, look, at least give me
the opportunity to explain.

1183
01:13:23,348 --> 01:13:26,044
Okay, but what's to explain?

1184
01:13:26,218 --> 01:13:30,678
That you're an immature man-child
who used me in your demented plot...

1185
01:13:30,856 --> 01:13:35,418
...to squeeze your mom's boyfriend out of
her life so that you could win her back?

1186
01:13:35,594 --> 01:13:39,655
Oh, yeah, and your long-distance girlfriend
is imaginary.

1187
01:13:39,832 --> 01:13:41,891
Does that about wrap it up there?

1188
01:13:42,067 --> 01:13:43,932
You're sick, bro.

1189
01:13:44,103 --> 01:13:47,436
It sounds a lot worse when you string it
all together like that, Richard.

1190
01:13:47,606 --> 01:13:49,198
-You can't go back there.
-Nora!

1191
01:13:49,374 --> 01:13:52,002
Don't even bother
filling out that application.

1192
01:13:53,512 --> 01:13:55,377
Where's your car?

1193
01:13:56,715 --> 01:14:01,084
I sold it. I'm taking a bus
to Austin next Sunday.

1194
01:14:01,253 --> 01:14:04,916
Nora, please. Give me another chance.

1195
01:14:06,024 --> 01:14:07,048
Why?

1196
01:14:07,226 --> 01:14:11,026
You don't care about me.
You don't care about anybody.

1197
01:14:15,567 --> 01:14:18,536
Do you have any idea
how much pain you caused your mom?

1198
01:14:19,371 --> 01:14:20,998
Do you?

1199
01:14:21,173 --> 01:14:24,267
All she wanted was a life,
and you went and you messed it up...

1200
01:14:24,443 --> 01:14:26,502
...because you're too afraid
to live your own.

1201
01:14:26,678 --> 01:14:28,703
There's no way
I'm letting you do that to me.

1202
01:14:28,881 --> 01:14:33,545
I'm chasing my dream.
I'm taking my shot, okay?

1203
01:14:33,719 --> 01:14:34,708
[SIGHS]

1204
01:14:34,887 --> 01:14:37,447
And if your mom knew
what was good for her, she would too.

1205
01:14:37,623 --> 01:14:40,183
And she'd kick you out
of that goddamn house.

1206
01:14:40,359 --> 01:14:42,054
She did.

1207
01:14:43,462 --> 01:14:44,451
[NORA SIGHS]

1208
01:14:44,630 --> 01:14:49,226
Oh. So, what?
I guess you need a place to crash?

1209
01:14:51,236 --> 01:14:55,002
God, you're so pathetic.

1210
01:16:27,699 --> 01:16:28,927
[URINATING]

1211
01:16:29,101 --> 01:16:32,093
[DISPATCHER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER POLICE RADIO]

1212
01:16:32,271 --> 01:16:33,966
[SIREN BLARES]

1213
01:16:36,942 --> 01:16:40,173
TRANSVESTITE:
Mm. Nummy-num-nums. Ahh.

1214
01:16:40,345 --> 01:16:41,403
COP:
Come on.

1215
01:16:41,580 --> 01:16:45,744
Thanks for coming.
I hope we can let bygones be bygones.

1216
01:16:46,952 --> 01:16:50,945
I just spent 500 dollars
to get you out of jail.

1217
01:16:51,123 --> 01:16:53,717
Then we're off to a good start.

1218
01:16:56,928 --> 01:17:00,659
Well, now, as you know,
there isn't much room.

1219
01:17:00,832 --> 01:17:03,164
-And there's only one bed.
-All right.

1220
01:17:03,335 --> 01:17:06,827
Are you sure you're gonna be okay
sleeping on the floor?

1221
01:17:10,042 --> 01:17:12,510
I was thinking
you would sleep on the floor.

1222
01:17:12,678 --> 01:17:14,908
I've got spina bifida.

1223
01:17:15,080 --> 01:17:17,071
I've got osteoporosis.

1224
01:17:17,249 --> 01:17:19,012
Well, I'm allergic to dust.

1225
01:17:19,184 --> 01:17:22,119
I'm 91 fucking years old.

1226
01:17:22,287 --> 01:17:23,754
[SEYMOUR SCOFFS]

1227
01:17:27,492 --> 01:17:29,551
JEFFREY:
Seymour, you awake?

1228
01:17:30,062 --> 01:17:31,962
I've been such a wiener.

1229
01:17:32,130 --> 01:17:33,791
What are you doing in my bed?

1230
01:17:33,965 --> 01:17:37,628
Do you think there's any way for me
to make redress for the things I've done?

1231
01:17:38,503 --> 01:17:40,596
It's 4:00 in the morning.

1232
01:17:40,772 --> 01:17:42,330
I need to know, Seymour.

1233
01:17:42,507 --> 01:17:46,637
Can I be redeemed
for all the suffering I've caused?

1234
01:17:47,979 --> 01:17:51,745
If you're looking for some wise,
pithy bit of advice...

1235
01:17:52,517 --> 01:17:57,614
...that only an old man with
a lifetime of experience can give you...

1236
01:17:57,789 --> 01:18:00,349
...you're barking up the wrong tree.

1237
01:18:04,763 --> 01:18:06,196
[SIGHS]

1238
01:18:06,365 --> 01:18:09,163
What I can tell you...

1239
01:18:09,334 --> 01:18:15,637
...is the love we give away
is the only love we keep.

1240
01:18:17,142 --> 01:18:21,135
That's actually wise and pithy, Seymour.

1241
01:18:21,313 --> 01:18:26,649
I got it off an old Deepak Chopra calendar.
I think it was September.

1242
01:18:26,952 --> 01:18:28,943
[GRUNTING]

1243
01:18:40,232 --> 01:18:41,631
Wake up, old man.

1244
01:18:41,800 --> 01:18:43,961
What in the name of Mike is going on?

1245
01:18:44,136 --> 01:18:45,262
I have a plan...

1246
01:18:45,437 --> 01:18:48,338
-...to restore order to the universe.
-Huh?

1247
01:18:48,507 --> 01:18:50,668
I'm getting my mother
back together with Mert.

1248
01:18:52,878 --> 01:18:54,937
You're wearing my suit.

1249
01:18:56,681 --> 01:18:57,875
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

1250
01:18:58,049 --> 01:18:59,414
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1251
01:18:59,584 --> 01:19:02,610
SEYMOUR: Slow down!
JEFFREY: I don't know how!

1252
01:19:02,788 --> 01:19:04,653
[HORN HONKING]

1253
01:19:04,823 --> 01:19:06,814
[INAUDIBLE]

1254
01:19:14,332 --> 01:19:15,321
[LAUGHS]

1255
01:19:18,203 --> 01:19:21,036
JEFFREY'S VOICE:
<i>"My dearest Jan, I've taken some time...</i>

1256
01:19:21,206 --> 01:19:23,606
<i>...out of my incredibly</i>
<i>successful schedule...</i>

1257
01:19:23,775 --> 01:19:26,801
<i>...to think about recent events,</i>
<i>and I've come to a conclusion.</i>

1258
01:19:26,978 --> 01:19:31,608
<i>I was wrong. Yes, I, Mert,</i>
<i>the meat magician, screwed up.</i>

1259
01:19:31,783 --> 01:19:36,117
<i>I just want you to know that I'm sorry,</i>
<i>and I know that Jeffrey is sorry.</i>

1260
01:19:36,288 --> 01:19:38,654
<i>What he did was selfish and childish.</i>

1261
01:19:38,824 --> 01:19:43,124
<i>He was afraid to live his own life, afraid</i>
<i>that by sharing you he would lose you...</i>

1262
01:19:43,295 --> 01:19:46,321
<i>...but he loves you</i>
<i>and he wants us to be together.</i>

1263
01:19:46,498 --> 01:19:50,332
<i>Please, meet me at Brentfield Park</i>
<i>tomorrow at 3.</i>

1264
01:19:50,502 --> 01:19:53,198
<i>All my love, Mert. "

1265
01:19:55,841 --> 01:19:59,504
<i>"Dear Mert, you're right.</i>
<i>Jeffrey should be on a leash.</i>

1266
01:19:59,678 --> 01:20:03,614
<i>Meet me at Brentfield Park tomorrow</i>
<i>at 3. Love, Jan. "

1267
01:20:03,782 --> 01:20:05,477
Yes!

1268
01:20:13,525 --> 01:20:16,119
JEFFREY:
Damn it, where is she?

1269
01:20:16,294 --> 01:20:18,888
Jeffrey, Jeffrey...

1270
01:20:20,165 --> 01:20:22,759
...no matter what happens
from here on out...

1271
01:20:22,934 --> 01:20:27,098
...I want you to know just one thing:
I'm proud of you.

1272
01:20:29,274 --> 01:20:31,572
SEYMOUR:
Subject in motion.

1273
01:20:33,945 --> 01:20:36,243
MERT [OVER SPEAKER] : <i>Hi.</i>
JAN: <i>Hi, you wanted to see me?</i>

1274
01:20:36,414 --> 01:20:40,851
Yes, yes, I did. I got your note.

1275
01:20:41,086 --> 01:20:44,487
-Oh. My what? My note?
-Ooh.

1276
01:20:44,656 --> 01:20:46,180
-Yeah.
-No, wait a minute.

1277
01:20:46,358 --> 01:20:48,326
I mean, you sent me a note. It's--

1278
01:20:48,493 --> 01:20:51,121
No, you wrote me a note. But, anyway.

1279
01:20:51,296 --> 01:20:53,764
Anyway, right, forget it.

1280
01:20:53,932 --> 01:20:55,991
MERT: <i>Jan, no, wait, wait, wait.</i>
<i>Whoa, whoa, whoa.</i>

1281
01:20:56,668 --> 01:21:00,229
Look, I know I should've come clean
about everything...

1282
01:21:00,405 --> 01:21:02,873
...but I just--
I was afraid I was gonna lose you.

1283
01:21:03,041 --> 01:21:04,030
[SCOFFS]

1284
01:21:04,209 --> 01:21:07,667
That sounds like an excuse,
but it's not, it's true.

1285
01:21:07,846 --> 01:21:10,314
Look, I....

1286
01:21:14,753 --> 01:21:19,588
I have been in love with you
since the first moment I saw you.

1287
01:21:20,458 --> 01:21:21,618
[WHISPERS]
Bingo.

1288
01:21:23,161 --> 01:21:24,185
[EXHALES]

1289
01:21:24,362 --> 01:21:26,193
JEFFREY:
What? Damn it!

1290
01:21:26,364 --> 01:21:28,798
Can't they do anything right?

1291
01:21:28,967 --> 01:21:30,025
What's happen--? What?

1292
01:21:33,638 --> 01:21:35,105
Oh! Oh.

1293
01:21:35,273 --> 01:21:36,968
Oh, my God.

1294
01:21:37,142 --> 01:21:39,303
Lovely day for a stroll.

1295
01:21:39,477 --> 01:21:41,411
Leave me alone, okay?

1296
01:21:41,580 --> 01:21:44,378
-Come on, give Mert another chance.
-What?

1297
01:21:44,549 --> 01:21:48,986
Look, I know I haven't always been
the world's greatest son, but he loves you.

1298
01:21:49,154 --> 01:21:53,284
And I know you love him too. Just give me
the opportunity to make things right.

1299
01:21:53,458 --> 01:21:54,652
[EXHALES]

1300
01:21:54,826 --> 01:21:58,694
Come on, I really am sorry.
For everything I've done.

1301
01:21:58,863 --> 01:22:00,490
-Since when?
-Since you met Mert.

1302
01:22:00,665 --> 01:22:03,463
-But what about before that?
-What are you referring to?

1303
01:22:03,635 --> 01:22:07,036
Well, I am referring to the fact
that you haven't been honest with me...

1304
01:22:07,205 --> 01:22:08,729
...a day in your life, Jeffrey.

1305
01:22:08,907 --> 01:22:11,273
-And you've been honest with me?
-No, I have not...

1306
01:22:11,443 --> 01:22:13,638
...and it just makes me absolutely sick.

1307
01:22:13,812 --> 01:22:16,007
To think that
our whole entire relationship...

1308
01:22:16,181 --> 01:22:19,116
...has been based on a foundation
of lies and self-deception--

1309
01:22:19,284 --> 01:22:21,252
This is no time
for a trip down memory lane.

1310
01:22:21,419 --> 01:22:23,580
It's not about us.
It's about you and Mert.

1311
01:22:23,755 --> 01:22:28,158
It's all about us.
It's all about where we went wrong.

1312
01:22:29,327 --> 01:22:33,229
-Don't you walk away from me, young lady.
-Don't you talk to me like that, young man.

1313
01:22:33,398 --> 01:22:34,626
I'm your mother.

1314
01:22:34,799 --> 01:22:38,826
I know. That's why I want you to be happy.
Don't you get it?

1315
01:22:39,004 --> 01:22:42,599
-That's why I want you to be with Mert.
-You can't handle it.

1316
01:22:42,774 --> 01:22:45,834
-What did you say?
-I said, you can't handle it.

1317
01:22:46,411 --> 01:22:51,644
I'm sorry, I didn't understand you because
the word "can't" isn't in my vocabulary.

1318
01:22:51,816 --> 01:22:53,010
[SIGHS]

1319
01:22:55,987 --> 01:22:59,150
Come here. Come here.

1320
01:22:59,324 --> 01:23:00,484
Come on.

1321
01:23:00,659 --> 01:23:02,092
[SIGHS]

1322
01:23:02,761 --> 01:23:04,820
[CLEARS THROAT]

1323
01:23:04,996 --> 01:23:07,692
[BOTH SIGH]

1324
01:23:09,134 --> 01:23:13,230
Come on, people.
Can't we put all this behind us?

1325
01:23:18,043 --> 01:23:20,534
-What--? What do we--?
-Come on.

1326
01:23:25,450 --> 01:23:26,747
[CLEARS THROAT]

1327
01:23:35,193 --> 01:23:36,490
Tsk.

1328
01:23:53,378 --> 01:23:56,370
All right, well,
sweetheart, please drive safe, okay?

1329
01:23:58,917 --> 01:24:00,009
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

1330
01:24:00,185 --> 01:24:03,086
-Do you need any cash?
-No, thanks.

1331
01:24:03,955 --> 01:24:06,788
You're a good man, Mert Rosenbloom.

1332
01:24:10,729 --> 01:24:11,923
[CHUCKLES]

1333
01:24:12,130 --> 01:24:13,859
Take care of my mother for me.

1334
01:24:14,032 --> 01:24:15,659
I will.

1335
01:24:27,045 --> 01:24:28,774
Bye.

1336
01:24:58,309 --> 01:24:59,867
What the hell is this?

1337
01:25:02,147 --> 01:25:05,139
[MORRISSEY'S "AMERICA IS NOT
THE WORLD" PLAYING OVER SPEAKER]

1338
01:25:09,954 --> 01:25:11,922
[PASSENGERS CHATTERING]

1339
01:25:21,766 --> 01:25:24,428
What is this? I'm on a schedule here.

1340
01:25:24,602 --> 01:25:25,591
[MUSIC DIES]

1341
01:25:25,770 --> 01:25:26,759
NORA:
Jeffrey.

1342
01:25:26,938 --> 01:25:29,429
-Is he your boyfriend?
-What the hell are you doing?

1343
01:25:29,607 --> 01:25:32,474
Trying to get this contraption to work.

1344
01:25:32,644 --> 01:25:35,238
-You're making a scene.
-Have you ever seen a shoddier...

1345
01:25:35,413 --> 01:25:37,779
...piece of equipment?
I may be forced to litigate.

1346
01:25:37,949 --> 01:25:41,476
-Move this vehicle or I'm calling the cops.
-I refuse to move an inch, sir...

1347
01:25:41,653 --> 01:25:44,121
...until the young lady agrees
to come with me.

1348
01:25:44,289 --> 01:25:45,881
Oh, my God.

1349
01:25:46,057 --> 01:25:47,957
-You're insane.
-No, I'm not.

1350
01:25:49,761 --> 01:25:51,888
I made a backup copy.

1351
01:25:52,964 --> 01:25:53,953
[SIGHS]

1352
01:25:54,132 --> 01:25:55,121
[HORN HONKING]

1353
01:25:55,300 --> 01:25:56,892
Look, Nora, you were right.

1354
01:25:57,068 --> 01:26:00,765
I was an asshole.
I'm sorry about the way I treated you.

1355
01:26:00,939 --> 01:26:03,737
It's just because I liked you so much.

1356
01:26:03,908 --> 01:26:06,468
What are you talking about?

1357
01:26:07,478 --> 01:26:12,472
You're smart,
you're intrepid, you're "funky."

1358
01:26:12,650 --> 01:26:16,051
I was just so terrified of being hurt...

1359
01:26:16,221 --> 01:26:17,745
...I couldn't admit it.

1360
01:26:17,922 --> 01:26:19,856
[HORNS HONKING]

1361
01:26:20,024 --> 01:26:21,787
But I'm not afraid anymore.

1362
01:26:22,360 --> 01:26:24,851
Now I'm late, asshole.
Move that piece of shit.

1363
01:26:25,029 --> 01:26:27,361
-Come make me, you philistine!
DRIVER: Ah....

1364
01:26:29,400 --> 01:26:31,766
Can you give me a chance?

1365
01:26:31,936 --> 01:26:34,404
Come with me?

1366
01:26:37,075 --> 01:26:38,064
[HORN HONKING]

1367
01:26:38,243 --> 01:26:39,801
MAN:
Get out of the way!

1368
01:26:41,446 --> 01:26:44,313
You sure you know
how to drive that thing?

1369
01:26:48,052 --> 01:26:50,043
[HONKING CONTINUES]

1370
01:26:58,096 --> 01:27:01,725
[HORN HONKING]

1371
01:27:01,900 --> 01:27:03,094
Sorry.

1372
01:27:03,268 --> 01:27:06,260
JEFFREY: <i>Dear Lunar Space Institute</i>
<i>of Austin, Texas:</i>

1373
01:27:06,437 --> 01:27:09,804
<i>A night of romance beneath the stars</i>
<i>with a plucky songstress...</i>

1374
01:27:09,974 --> 01:27:13,000
<i>...has reawakened me</i>
<i>to the majesty of the cosmos.</i>

1375
01:27:13,177 --> 01:27:16,112
<i>I have come to realize</i>
<i>that we are, all of us, connected.</i>

1376
01:27:16,281 --> 01:27:20,308
<i>And that, like the universe itself,</i>
<i>our dreams know no bounds.</i>

1377
01:27:20,485 --> 01:27:25,115
<i>My dream is to be an astronomer.</i>
<i>I look forward to seeing you in the fall.</i>

1378
01:27:25,290 --> 01:27:28,054
<i>And trust that I will not be assigned</i>
<i>a roommate this time...</i>

1379
01:27:28,226 --> 01:27:33,007
<i>...per my doctor's request.</i>
<i>Yours, Jeffrey Mannus.</i>

1380
01:32:59,824 --> 01:33:01,815
Subtitles by LeapinLar

